title: Man seriously injured after shooting in Parkway Village | News | fox13memphis.com
text:
2 men seriously injured after shooting in Parkway Village, MPD says FOX13 Memphis News Staff FOX13 Memphis News Staff Author facebook Author twitter Author email Apr 25, 2024 2 hrs ago Facebook Twitter WhatsApp SMS Email Facebook Twitter WhatsApp SMS Email Print Copy article link Save Facebook Twitter WhatsApp SMS Email Print Copy article link Save MEMPHIS, Tenn. - Gunfire in Parkway Village left two men seriously injured Thursday afternoon, according to the Memphis Police Department (MPD).
The bullets rang out around 1:30 p.m. in the 2700 block of Getwell Road, MPD said. When FOX13 crews arrived crime scene tape blocked off the gas pumps of an Exxon gas station in the area. Two police cars also blocked off the gas station.
MPD said a man was found with a gunshot wound. He was taken to Regional One Hospital in critical condition.
Around 1:41 p.m., police said officers got a call about a man being at Baptist Hospital with a gunshot wound.
Police said the man is also in critical condition and believe the man was shot at the same Getwell Road scene.
No information about the shooter or shooters was immediately released.

author: AOL Staff
title: Police release video of persons of interest in killing of pregnant Texas teen
text: Police release video of persons of interest in killing of pregnant Texas teen The San Antonio Police Department on Thursday released video of two persons of interest in the [shooting deaths of a pregnant teenager and her boyfriend](https://www.cbsnews.com/news/search-pregnant-teen-savanah-nicole-soto-texas/?ftag=YHF4eb9d17). Savanah Nicole Soto, 18, and her boyfriend, Matthew Guerra, 22, were both reported missing last week before they were [found dead in Guerra's car](https://www.cbsnews.com/news/savanah-nicole-soto-texas-pregnant-teen-death-family-speaks-out/?ftag=YHF4eb9d17) on Tuesday, family members said. Police said each of the victims had a gunshot wound. The couple disappeared a day before Soto, who was 9 months pregnant, was scheduled to be in induced to give birth. The medical examiner's office confirmed one of the bodies found was Guerra. The second victim has not been positively identified, but was described as a "full-term pregnant female," and San Antonio Police Chief Bill McManus said Thursday police are "confident" the second victim is Soto. The video released Thursday shows a person of interest driving a dark pickup truck and another person driving Guerra's Kia Optima "nearby where the bodies were found," the police department wrote on Facebook. This is a developing story and will be updated.
